message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The patient shows symptoms of cranial nerve involvement, specifically CN IX, X, and XI, which all pass through the jugular foramen. Foramen spinosum transmits the middle meningeal artery, foramen lacerum is filled by cartilage and located between the sphenoid and petrous part of the temporal bone, and foramen rotundum transmits the maxillary nerve.
